    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-27T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-27T06:00:00-05:00" n="810"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d810">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">674.84A/4–2754: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 810<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_RFH1" type="from"
                            >Russell</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d810fn1">Also sent to Cairo as telegram 85.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-27T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 27, 1954—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1114. Reference Cairo telegram 74 (1348 to Department)<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d810fn2">
                        <ref target="#d809">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> and <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1071 to
                    Department (82 to Cairo).<note n="3" xml:id="d810fn3">
                        <ref target="#d798">Document 798</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Foreign Ministry informed Embassy this morning: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Desires meet with <persName corresp="#p_RGM1">Riad</persName> though
                            would have no objection to <persName corresp="#p_GLCS1">Gohar</persName>
                            or other representative also being present.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> representatives will be Lt. Colonel
                            Shalev (IDF) and <persName corresp="#p_DS1">Samuel Divon</persName>
                            (recently of Israel Embassy, and currently advisor on Middle East
                            affairs in Foreign Ministry).</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Would prefer meeting without <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                            observer present but will acquiesce if <persName corresp="#p_RGM1"
                                >Riad</persName> wishes.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Latest developments indicate desirability of early meeting and suggest
                            Thursday or even Wednesday (tomorrow).</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>Suggests <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> be informed through this
                            Embassy of <persName corresp="#p_RGM1">Riad</persName>’s wishes as to
                            time and place of rendezvous of cars and place of meeting (presumably
                            Beersheba or Gaza).</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
